Reasoning: The paper discusses a MAC protocol for wireless local area networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of a deterministic backoff and hysteresis, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY), respectively. The paper also mentions the use of commercial hardware and open-source firmware, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
